cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

The paper deals with saliency estimation, which is a computer vision task. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also introduces a new deep learning architecture and novel loss functions, which are related to machine learning and artificial intelligence, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely sub-categories as well. The paper also mentions the use of large-scale datasets, which suggests the use of neural networks, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper evaluates its method on public benchmark datasets, which suggests the use of metrics and evaluation methods, making cs.MM (Multimedia) a possible sub-category.
